eMail client in BASH

REQUIREMENTS

A working GNU environment having bash, cat, clear, date, echo, grep,
kill, less, mv, printf and rm.

CONFIGURATION

Create ".readmailrc" in your home directory and put the following lines
into it (fill in the values in brackets):

pop.host: (your POP3 server)
pop.port: 110
pop.account: (your POP3 account)
pop.password: (your POP3 password)

Append this block to configure your SMTP settings:

smtp.host: (your SMTP server)
smtp.port: 25
smtp.account: (your SMTP account)
smtp.password: (your SMTP password, this is optional)

You may also add a optional notification command:

notification: xmessage "You've got mail" &
